00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:47,830
Er, what business might you have in coming to our rural town?

252
00:10:47,830 --> 00:10:49,870
Oh, I'm just here to conduct an inspection.

253
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,700
An inspection?

254
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:54,650
If only you had contacted me, 
I would've sent someone to meet you.

255
00:10:54,650 --> 00:10:58,880
You must be exhausted, right? 
Come, come, please stay at my mansion!

256
00:11:01,830 --> 00:11:03,010
Miserable dogs of the military!

257
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:10,300
Congratulations, Mustang-kun.

258
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:13,020
I hear you're going to 
become a full colonel soon.

259
00:11:13,420 --> 00:11:16,180
Hawkeye-kun, I hear you're going to be promoted to 1st Lieutenant too.

260
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:18,560
Thank you so much, General Hakuro.

261
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,900
I wonder, once your authority increases,

262
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:24,030
if you would go to the Eastern Command
Center and take charge of it for a while?

263
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:25,910
Oh, you're demoting me?

264
00:11:25,910 --> 00:11:29,070
I suppose having someone like me around Central does—

265
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:29,070
What are you talking about?

266
00:11:29,070 --> 00:11:32,250
This isn't a demotion. It's a transfer to a higher post, <i>Colonel</i> Mustang.

267
00:11:33,020 --> 00:11:35,880
However, I've heard there are a good number of untrustworthy folks in the Eastern Division.

268
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:37,930
Be sure to watch yourself.

269
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:43,500
I am greatly honored that a State Alchemist 
should come visit my house.

270
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:47,760
Oh, yes indeed. Since we have such an exceptional alchemist among us,

271
00:11:48,070 --> 00:11:51,100
Lyra, have him take 
a look at your alchemy.

272
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,260
Yes, sir.

273
00:11:52,260 --> 00:11:53,980
Nah, I saw it earlier.

274
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:57,550
She liquefied the air around her, 
reduced its volume,

275
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:00,280
and then all at once vaporized it again, 
producing a shockwave.

276
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:05,230
The light came from the extreme heat that was created by the forced compression, to maintain entropy.

277
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:07,620
You figured all that out 
with just a glance?

278
00:12:07,930 --> 00:12:11,360
I, too, would like to be certified as a State Alchemist

279
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:13,400
and become like you, Edward-sama.

280
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,630
Like me?

281
00:12:14,630 --> 00:12:15,660
Yes.

282
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:19,630
It is my dream to become an outstanding alchemist, 
and do all that I can for the state.

283
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:24,020
Now, now, please feel free to eat up.

284
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:27,140
I hope that our rural cooking will agree with you.

285
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,960
You eat well, huh?

286
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,830
Despite the town being in this shape...

287
00:12:32,830 --> 00:12:35,960
Oh, you embarrass me! 
The tax collecting has not been going well,

288
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,360
and I don't know 
what I'm going to do.

289
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:42,320
On top of that, there are so many 
barbaric residents here, as you saw earlier.

290
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:46,870
You mean, all they do is assert their rights and neglect their duty to pay their taxes?

291
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:51,220
Oh, indeed, Edward-sama, 
you are a man of understanding.

292
00:12:51,220 --> 00:12:54,760
You can express all the reasoning of the world 
in terms of equivalent exchange,

293
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:57,950
the basis of alchemy, you see.

294
00:12:57,950 --> 00:13:00,380
Rights come with responsibilities, don't they?

295
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:03,250
Certainly! Mm, most wonderful!

296
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:06,500
As such, I wonder if you would accept this,

297
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,730
by way of the reasoning of the world?

298
00:13:08,730 --> 00:13:09,640
Lyra?

299
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:14,440
It is only a small token. 
Please accept it.

300
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,650
Is this what you would call a bribe?

301
00:13:16,650 --> 00:13:18,550
That's far too direct a way of putting it.

302
00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:21,650
If you'd like, call it an equivalent exchange.

303
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:25,360
And if you would please consider the matter of the inspection...

304
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,240
I'll think about it.

305
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:31,680
I should have known that you would be so understanding, Edward-sama!

306
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:34,750
The folks in town should start 
behaving themselves soon enough,

307
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:37,050
so if you would care to wait briefly.

308
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:44,050
I wonder if Brother is all right on his own.

309
00:13:49,020 --> 00:13:50,640
Hey, what's going on?

310
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:00,810
Khayal! Khayal!

311
00:14:00,810 --> 00:14:03,070
Let go of me! Khayal is still in there!

312
00:14:03,070 --> 00:14:06,160
You can't, boss! It's too dangerous! 
There's no telling when it'll collapse!

313
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,300
Leave me alone! Let go of me!

314
00:14:07,300 --> 00:14:09,240
Boss!

315
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,240
Khayal!

316
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:16,170
Khayal! Khayal!

317
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:18,600
Khayal! Khayal, where are you?!

318
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,180
Khayal! Khayal!

319
00:14:21,180 --> 00:14:22,670
Daddy!

320
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:29,100
Daddy...

321
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:41,560
Is this their doing?

322
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:42,600
Mm-hmm.

323
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:47,070
Say, you're a cracker-jack alchemist, right?

324
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:50,200
So then, transmute some gold for us!

325
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:51,570
Then you can help my pop...

326
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:54,000
You could save the whole town for us!

327
00:14:54,830 --> 00:14:55,580
I can't.

328
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:57,700
Why not?! You don't lose anything!

329
00:14:57,930 --> 00:15:01,120
The basis of alchemy is equivalent exchange.

330
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:04,330
I have neither the duty nor the obligation to do anything for this town.

331
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:08,520
Are you telling us to bribe you as well?!

332
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,800
And you call yourself an alchemist?!

333
00:15:12,030 --> 00:15:15,890
"Alchemist, be thou for the People," huh?

334
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:20,050
Transmuting gold is a serious offense.

335
00:15:20,050 --> 00:15:23,870
If I get caught, I'll be stripped of 
my State Alchemist certification,

336
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:25,260
and sent to prison.

337
00:15:25,260 --> 00:15:26,540
So, do it so no one finds out!

338
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:30,130
Even if I do make gold, it'll just be taken in taxes, and that'll be the end of it.

339
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:32,810
If you're really that hard up,

340
00:15:32,810 --> 00:15:36,060
why don't you leave this town and go find some other work?

341
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,410
Kid,

342
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:39,750
you may not understand this,

343
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:43,630
but this place is our home, and our coffin.

344
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:53,130
This is your home and coffin, huh?

345
00:15:53,790 --> 00:15:55,010
Brother!

346
00:15:55,010 --> 00:15:58,010
Al, we burned down our home ourselves.

347
00:15:58,380 --> 00:16:02,020
We have nowhere to return to, 
and that's all right by us.

348
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:04,440
But for people who do have somewhere they call home,

349
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,480
they have to look out for it.

350
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:12,450
Al, what you see here will be our secret.

351
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:24,370
Brother...

352
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,880
You want to buy the coal mine?!

353
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:31,710
Yeah! I want you to include everything from the mine to the trade routes.

354
00:16:31,710 --> 00:16:32,260
Is that okay?

355
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:37,100
Well... even at the request of a State Alchemist, that's just something I couldn't...

356
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:40,130
I see. That's a shame.

357
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:44,140
And here I got all this money ready...

358
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,150
I-Is that...

359
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,280
all gold?!

360
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,800
Upon investigation, 
it turns out that this mine

361
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,440
had unexploited elements that we use in alchemy research.

362
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:55,320
I don't want to turn it 
over to anyone else.

363
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,820
Is this enough?

364
00:16:56,820 --> 00:16:59,030
Don't be absurd!

365
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:03,350
However, my selling the mine that 
I was entrusted by the state to govern

366
00:17:03,350 --> 00:17:06,210
for my own profit will look a little...

367
00:17:06,210 --> 00:17:09,780
It's all right! This gold doesn't appear on any records,

368
00:17:09,780 --> 00:17:13,140
so as long as you keep your lips sealed, 
you can get by without anyone else knowing.

369
00:17:13,140 --> 00:17:14,130
Still...

370
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:16,170
I know!

371
00:17:16,170 --> 00:17:20,750
Please write up a memo handing over all authority over the coal mine for no charge.

372
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:25,050
By doing that, this will be 
all yours, Lieutenant Yoki.

373
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,150
Why?!

374
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,400
Why are you stopping me?!

375
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,990
I just am! I will not allow you to fight!

376
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:37,420
But they were the ones who demolished the store!

377
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:39,200
It's just one store.

378
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,570
Don't get so fired up.

379
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:45,250
Hi, everybody! I'm here to cheer up 
those gloomy faces of yours!

380
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:47,100
What are you doing here?!

381
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:51,630
Now, now, is that any way to 
talk to the manager of this place?

382
00:17:51,630 --> 00:17:54,550
Manager?! Why, you! 
What have you—

383
00:17:54,550 --> 00:17:58,790
As you can see, this is the title deed for the mining, trade, management,

384
00:17:58,790 --> 00:18:00,470
and all other rights 
to this coal mine.

385
00:18:00,470 --> 00:18:01,300
What?!

386
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:05,810
In other words, right now, 
this coal mine belongs to me.

387
00:18:06,730 --> 00:18:07,810
Nevertheless...

388
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:11,420
I have to go back to Central.

389
00:18:11,420 --> 00:18:13,950
It would be a nuisance to have to 
carry this title deed back with me.

390
00:18:13,950 --> 00:18:15,820
What to do?

391
00:18:15,820 --> 00:18:19,030
Don't tell me you're 
trying to sell that to us!

392
00:18:19,030 --> 00:18:20,270
It'll cost an arm and a leg!

393
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:22,000
Whenever you wish to gain anything,

394
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,790
you have to pay for it with something of appropriate value, you see.

395
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:29,000
After all, not only is this title deed written on high-grade parchment,

396
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,000
it also has gold leaf trim.

397
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,650
What's more, the box 
features finely crushed jade,

398
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:36,760
in a nonchalant yet luxurious design.

399
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:39,320
Yeah, this is real craftsmanship, all right.

400
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:42,350
Oh yeah, and the key is made of sterling silver.

401
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:45,680
Gee, I would roughly estimate that it's worth 200,000.

402
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:48,560
200,000?! For the deed to the coal mine?!

403
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,080
200,000?!

404
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:51,120
That's all?!

405
00:18:51,810 --> 00:18:55,400
Come to mention it, the foreman's inn 
cost 200,000, didn't it?

406
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:57,320
How about I spend the night and we call it even?

407
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,580
Equivalent exchange, huh?

408
00:19:00,580 --> 00:19:02,570
But our inn has been...

409
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:06,200
Huh? Well then, 
what's that over there?

410
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,480
Our shop!

411
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:13,030
How can this be?!

412
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:16,050
This will be enough to 
cover me staying here, right?

413
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:19,550
Yeah, of course it will.

414
00:19:19,550 --> 00:19:21,630
Okay, then it's an equivalent exchange!

415
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:24,550
Edward-sama!

416
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:26,240
Wh-What's going on here?!

417
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,770
The gold bars that I got from you 
have all turned to stone!

418
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:31,360
Gold bars? Why, whatever are you talking about?

419
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,770
Please don't play dumb!

420
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:35,770
I traded you that title deed 
for a mountain of gold bars!

421
00:19:35,770 --> 00:19:40,450
Huh? You handed over the deed free of charge, didn't you?

422
00:19:40,450 --> 00:19:42,780
Look, I even have the memo here.

423
00:19:43,660 --> 00:19:44,960
Y-You swindled me!

424
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:48,750
"Swindled" makes it sound so scandalous. It was a legitimate transaction.

425
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:51,250
The transaction is invalid! Lyra!

426
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:02,010
Alchemist, be thou for the People!

427
00:20:02,010 --> 00:20:05,090
I don't much care for you using 
alchemy for your own interests!

428
00:20:05,090 --> 00:20:07,320
You're a State Alchemist, aren't you?!

429
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:09,400
Why would you go against what the military is doing?!

430
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:20,440
I never sold my soul to them.

431
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:48,600
Why, you...

432
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,270
Get the title deed back from—

433
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:53,270
Yoki-sama...

434
00:20:54,260 --> 00:20:58,510
You shouldn't take other people's personal property from them by force, huh?

435
00:20:58,510 --> 00:21:02,560
Never underestimate the strength of a coal mining man, Lieutenant!

436
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:10,240
Saké! Saké! Bring us some saké!

437
00:21:11,730 --> 00:21:15,250
Say, honey, isn't the shop 
a little better than before?

438
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:17,790
Yeah. He really did a number here...

439
00:21:19,490 --> 00:21:23,260
Edward Elric, the Fullmetal Alchemist.

440
00:21:25,170 --> 00:21:27,900
This is the report from Edward Elric.

441
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:28,680
Thanks.

442
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:32,020
I hear this will provide the chance to reevaluate Youswell Coal Mine

443
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:35,180
and the personnel at the Eastern Command Center who oversee it.

444
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:36,550
Really?

445
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:39,850
That'll probably make it 
a little easier to live out east.

446
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:42,940
Rejoice! Even if we are relocated, we'll be able to take it easy.

447
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:45,820
Don't tell me you meant for 
this to happen from the start!

448
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:50,770
Perhaps. More importantly, it would be nice 
if the women in the east were pretty.

449
00:21:50,770 --> 00:21:54,950
Also, their reputations are quickly spreading throughout the east.

450
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:59,460
They're saying that there is a champion of the people among the dogs of the military.

